Tour Edge Men's Bazooka HT Max-D Hybrid
column5:
This classic pear-shaped Tour Edge Men's Bazooka HT Max-D hybrid offers stunning good looks, an aerodynamic design and advanced weighting to deliver a higher moment of inertia (MOI, the club’s ability to resist twisting and impart greater force). The Bazooka features two internal weight cavities in the heel and toe that lower the center of gravity and move it deeper in the club head for a high launch and great forgiveness.
Helping you hit longer, better feeling shots, the HT Max-D has an ultra-thin, forged face compliments of crown-pull technology that minimizes thickness and maximizes strength. Add a maraging steel head with an oversized sweet spot and you have a hybrid that is capable of delivering some of the most consistent and accurate shots you’ve ever hit.
column8: Aerodynamic head design increases club head speed on every shot.
column9: Ultra-thin forged face delivers powerful distance from more contact points.
column10: Tour Edge Aldila NV-65 shaft delivers outstanding launch characteristics.

Tour Edge Men's Bazooka HT Max-D Combo Set 4-5 HY/6-SW
column5:
The Tour Edge Men's Bazooka HT Max-D Combo Set brings distance and accuracy perfectly combined with its two hybrids (4H, 5H) and six irons (6-SW).
"This classic pear-shaped hybrid offers stunning good looks, an aerodynamic design and advanced weighting to deliver a higher moment of inertia (MOI, the club’s ability to resist twisting and impart greater force). The Bazooka features two internal weight cavities in the heel and toe that lower the center of gravity and move it deeper in the club head for a high launch and great forgiveness.
The set’s progressive design can be seen in each iron’s different blade length, face height, top line, offset, bounce and MOI. This optimizes the club’s performance in distance, trajectory, spin, bounce, forgiveness and accuracy."
column8: The mid iron # 6 features a shorter blade length, less offset, more bounce and a smaller top line and sole for greater workability and shot making.
column9: The scoring irons (8-SW) feature a smaller undercut cavity, the least offset, the most bounce and a slightly larger sole than the mid irons for shots that get up quickly and stick close to the pin.

Tour Edge Men's Bazooka HT Max-D Driver
column5:
The Tour Edge Bazooka HT Max-D Super Light driver delivers stunning power off the tee and faster swing speeds not possible from traditional drivers.  The head's sloped crown and aerodynamic shape reduce drag and improve airflow to generate super-fast swing speed and explosive rebound off the face.  Powering this is a 46" remarkably light 50-gram Aldila shaft designed from Tour Edge incredibly popular NV platform.
The 460cc titanium head offers the ultimate combination of distance and forgiveness.  The deep face and huge sweet spot deliver maximum power from more launch points.  Harnessing the driver's power, two internal weight cavities in the rear sole move weight back in the heel and toe for maximum stability.  The combination of a large effective hitting area and advanced weighting technology delivers explosive power and accuracy even on off center hits.
column8: New more-aerodynamic head shape increases club speed for more power.
column9: Deep face and huge sweet spot produce powerful drives from more contact points.
column10: Tour Edge Aldila NV shaft delivers consistent, exceptional performance on every drive.

Tour Edge Men's Bazooka HT Max-D Fairway Wood
column5:
The Bazooka HT Max-D Fairway Wood is lightweight, sleek and delivers more distance for your buck than any fairway wood on the market. With this Bazooka, power is enhanced by the visible sloped crown and aerodynamic shape that reduce drag and improve airflow for enhanced swing speed and faster ball speed. Additional technology includes the commanding, ultra-light, 65-gram, 43” Tour Edge Aldila NV shaft that generates greater club head speed and longer hits. 
For extra accuracy, the Bazooka has a high moment of inertia (MOI), the club’s ability to resist twisting and impart greater force. The club features two internal weight cavities in the heel and toe that lower the center of gravity and move it deeper in the head for a higher (MOI). In addition, the deeper than traditional club head from front to back moves the center of gravity further away from the face for a high launch and remarkable forgiveness.
column8: Hyper-steel head with super-thin face launches the ball higher and longer.
column9: Variable face thickness provides larger effective hitting area for unsurpassed consistency.
column10: Features Aldila-designed shaft based on their NV shaft series.

Tour Edge Men's Bazooka HT Max Hybrid
column5:
The Tour Edge Men's Bazooka HT Max hybrid delivers advanced technology at an affordable price, and permits long and accurate shots.
Incorporating advanced heel-toe weighting, the Bazooka HT Max has four internal weight cavities in the heel and toe that lower the center of gravity and move it deeper in the club head for a higher moment of inertia (MOI - the club’s ability to resist twisting and to impart greater force on the ball). This helps the Bazooka deliver longer, more accurate shots than competitive hybrids.
The HT Max hybrid is cast using crown-pull technology that results in a thinner crown and face. Add a shallow face design and fixed weight screw for a lower center of gravity, and this hybrid is capable of delivering consistent, accurate shots. The HT’s hyper-steel head also boasts an expanded face size for an oversized sweet spot and larger effective hitting area. Combined with the ultra-thin face technology, the HT delivers longer shots, even on off-center hits.
column8: Four internal weight cavities in the heel and toe for superior stability.
column9: 20-gram tungsten sole weight provides a deeper, lower center of gravity.
column10: Ultra-thin face technology rockets the ball from more points on the face.
